# Website content is hand-curated (do not overwrite)

This portfolio site is **not** generated from `content_manifest.json` for day-to-day edits. Treat live files as authoritative.

## Source of truth

| Artifact | Role |
|----------|------|
| `pages/*.html` | **Canonical** page content, galleries, captions, videos |
| `index.html` | **Canonical** home (has `INDEX_CURATED` ‚Äî do not regenerate) |
| `site.css` | **Canonical** layout (has `SITE_CSS_LOCKED` ‚Äî do not run `write_styles`) |
| `markdowns/*.md` | Source for pages that use markdown (e.g. `Double_Yc`) |
| `content_manifest.json` | **Derived** crawl/archive ‚Äî update FROM pages, not the other way around |

## Forbidden unless the user explicitly asks

- Running `archive/generate_site.py --regenerate-pages` or `--force`
- Rewriting `pages/*.html` body from `content_manifest.json`
- Bulk-regenerating section pages while adding SEO, sitemap, or tooling
- Removing `media-pair` / `media-triplet` / `media-quad` layouts, `media-caption` blocks, `<video>`, or `caption-label` (Left/Right) copy
- Changing gallery **formatting** in `site.css` (pair heights, caption spacing, column ratios) without a specific user request

## Allowed without asking (narrow)

- `python archive/generate_site.py` with **no flags** ‚Üí only `robots.txt` + `sitemap.xml` (+ `sitemap-images.xml` when `seo/image_alt.json` exists)
- `python archive/seo_apply_all.py` ‚Üí refresh `seo/image_alt.json`, apply `img` alts, regenerate sitemaps
- `python archive/sync_manifest_from_pages.py` when user wants manifest synced **from** HTML
- Editing a **specific** page/section the user named in the current task
- Adding SEO `<head>` tags **without** changing `<section class="media-list">` body

## SEO scripts (metadata only ‚Äî no visible copy)

- **`seo/image_alt.json`**: derived alt text from figcaptions / index cards; not shown on page
- **`archive/apply_image_seo.py`**: may change only `img alt` and `title` attributes
- **`archive/seo_heads.py`**: may change only `<head>` (meta, JSON-LD, favicons)
- Do **not** run `seo_heads.patch_html_file` bulk over all pages unless the user asks ‚Äî it rewrites entire `<head>` blocks

## Before changing layout or restoring content

1. **Read** the file and match existing patterns (`media-pair--*`, `figcaption.media-caption--tight`, `caption-label`).
2. If recovering lost content, prefer **`git show e5ddac1:pages/<slug>.html`** (or user-named commit), merge body + keep current SEO head ‚Äî **not** manifest regeneration.
3. If a page has galleries (`class="media-pair"`), it is curated ‚Äî treat as restore-only from git or surgical edits.

## Optional marker

Add `<!-- PAGE_CURATED -->` in the first ~20 lines of a page to document that it must not be manifest-regenerated.
